{
  "stem": "24242.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 13 SECONDS] We were living like-- I guess it's known to the world-- like farmers live [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] up until the 22nd of June, 1941, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] when the Nazis occupied the whole area.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Be my guest.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was an older-- Walter was already-- I'm-- what I am giving you the information is what I remember.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At those days, Tuvia was somewhere else, like [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 300 kilometers away from our farm.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was married and living a-- as a merchant.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Then I had another brother, Nathan, which was in America later on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He went in the very low '30s, came to America.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A good question, which I don't know if I could answer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I asked later on, why didn't my parents leave?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the answer was it was very hard to get a visa to the United States, and financial hardship.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It wasn't so easy to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] leave to another country.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But after those two fellows-- Walter and Nathan, who had an uncle here in the United States, and he sent [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a girl to pick them up, in other words, one at a time.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this is the way those two brothers were lucky enough to get to the United States.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, got married there, and this is the way-- later on-- that was before my time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was born in 1930, and the oldest was born in 1904.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I should say so.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other one, Nathan, was born in 1913.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] At home lived another one, Abraham, Yankel, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and Asael.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were before my time.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
